<div id="outline-container-org013798c" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org013798c">My OS</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org013798c">
<p>
My <b>current</b> daily driver is <code>GuixOS</code>, a GNU/Linux distro based on the <code>guix</code> package manager.
Guix is a functional pkg manager, highly inspired by <a href="https://nixos.org/">Nix</a>.
</p>

<p>
As it shouldn't be suprising, by default there <b>isn't any</b> non-free software in guix's repos.
Talking about non-free software, Guix System uses <code>Linux libre</code> instead of the full Linux kernel. The reason for that is quite obvious. There are some proprietary blobs in the kernel (drivers..).
</p>

<p>
Of course, the community found a way around these limitations. There is a <a href="https://gitlab.com/nonguix/nonguix">repo</a> with non-free software. Also, <a href="https://youtube.com/channel/UCAiiOTio8Yu69c3XnR7nQBQ">System Crafters</a> provides a custom ISO with the full Linux kernel and the repo already set up.
</p>
</div>
</div>

